text: Hana Matelová (born 8 June 1990 in Zlín)Profile at Sports-Reference.com is a Czech table tennis player. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's singles event, in which she was eliminated in the first round by Zhang Mo. She won the French Championship with ASRTT Etival Clairefontaine on 2018-2019 season. ==References== Category:1990 births Category:Czech female table tennis players Category:Sportspeople from Zlín Category:Olympic table tennis players of the Czech Republic Category:Table tennis players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Living people Category:Table tennis players at the 2015 European Games Category:European Games competitors for the Czech Republic Category:European Games medalists in table tennis Category:European Games bronze medalists for the Czech Republic Category:Table tennis players at the 2019 European Games
